        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 2.  LOAN FOR CONSUMPTION ( MUTUUM )
Art. 2904.  Loan for consumption; definition
The loan for consumption is a contract by which a person, the lender, delivers consumable things to another, the borrower, who binds himself to return to the lender an equal amount of things of the same kind and quality.</p>
